The paper deals with distributed computing and fault tolerance, which are core topics in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and lower bounds, which are relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper discusses Byzantine faults, which are a type of security threat, making the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category a likely fit. The paper also involves synchronization and consistency, which are topics in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information theory, which is a topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
